==English==

===Etymology===
From [[know]] + [[it]] + [[all]]

===Noun===
'''know-it-all''' (plural: '''know-it-alls''')

# [[Someone]] who acts as if he/she knows [[everything]] and [[believes]] him/herself above others as a result (usually not a [[compliment]])
#: ''I had it figured out, but this '''know-it-all''' marched in with a better idea.''

